        "created_at": "2021-07-29T05:02:09.226Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Amusingly, most banking systems aren\u2019t implemented like that at all and instead use compensating transactions. Using it for likes/dislikes should work great though with some extra work for batching when there are hot keys. Generally though there are a bunch of ways to model problems and the specific use case should be examined before designing the best solution. At small scale, you can just build it naively using transactions and it will work.</p>",
